cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LT, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a logic for true concurrency. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with the description of events in computations. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper contributes to a deeper understanding of the relations between behavioural equivalences, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.LT (Language and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with the description of causal dependencies in computations, which is related to automata theory. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a possible category as the paper proposes an extension of the logic with fixpoint operators, which is related to formal languages and automata theory.
